  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 17 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 8 critical, 9 high, 15 medium, 7 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK), Cluj Avram Iancu (CLJ/LRCL) and Chişinău (RMO/LUKK); plus 14 other bases. 15 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and cold‑temperature performance penalties  — most notably around Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP), Bucharest Băneasa Aurel Vlaicu (BBU/LRBS) and Chişinău (RMO/LUKK). Network hotspots: Kaunas (KUN/EYKA), Bucharest Băneasa Aurel Vlaicu (BBU/LRBS), Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Trondheim Airport, Værnes (TRD/ENVA) and 12 others. Primary drivers: snow / blowing snow, low cloud base and mist. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Turku (TKU/EFTU), Trondheim Airport, Værnes (TRD/ENVA), Debrecen (DEB/LHDC) and 9 others.",
